.SS "bench, abench"
.IX Subsection "bench, abench"
Benchmark part of a filtergraph.
.PP
The filter accepts the following options:
.IP "\fBaction\fR" 4
.IX Item "action"
Start or stop a timer.
.Sp
Available values are:
.RS 4
.IP "\fBstart\fR" 4
.IX Item "start"
Get the current time, set it as frame metadata (using the key
\&\f(CW\*(C`lavfi.bench.start_time\*(C'\fR), and forward the frame to the next filter.
.IP "\fBstop\fR" 4
.IX Item "stop"
Get the current time and fetch the \f(CW\*(C`lavfi.bench.start_time\*(C'\fR metadata from
the input frame metadata to get the time difference. Time difference, average,
maximum and minimum time (respectively \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`avg\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`max\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`min\*(C'\fR) are then printed. The timestamps are expressed in seconds.
.RE
.RS 4
