.SS "showvolume"
.IX Subsection "showvolume"
Convert input audio volume to a video output.
.PP
The filter accepts the following options:
.IP "\fBrate, r\fR" 4
.IX Item "rate, r"
Set video rate.
.IP "\fBb\fR" 4
.IX Item "b"
Set border width, allowed range is [0, 5]. Default is 1.
.IP "\fBw\fR" 4
.IX Item "w"
Set channel width, allowed range is [80, 8192]. Default is 400.
.IP "\fBh\fR" 4
.IX Item "h"
Set channel height, allowed range is [1, 900]. Default is 20.
.IP "\fBf\fR" 4
.IX Item "f"
Set fade, allowed range is [0, 1]. Default is 0.95.
.IP "\fBc\fR" 4
.IX Item "c"
Set volume color expression.
.Sp
The expression can use the following variables:
.RS 4
.IP "\fB\s-1VOLUME\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "VOLUME"
Current max volume of channel in dB.
.IP "\fB\s-1PEAK\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "PEAK"
Current peak.
.IP "\fB\s-1CHANNEL\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "CHANNEL"
Current channel number, starting from 0.
.RE
.RS 4
.RE
.IP "\fBt\fR" 4
.IX Item "t"
If set, displays channel names. Default is enabled.
.IP "\fBv\fR" 4
.IX Item "v"
If set, displays volume values. Default is enabled.
.IP "\fBo\fR" 4
.IX Item "o"
Set orientation, can be horizontal: \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR or vertical: \f(CW\*(C`v\*(C'\fR,
default is \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR.
.IP "\fBs\fR" 4
.IX Item "s"
Set step size, allowed range is [0, 5]. Default is 0, which means
step is disabled.
.IP "\fBp\fR" 4
.IX Item "p"
Set background opacity, allowed range is [0, 1]. Default is 0.
.IP "\fBm\fR" 4
.IX Item "m"
Set metering mode, can be peak: \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR or rms: \f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR,
default is \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR.
.IP "\fBds\fR" 4
.IX Item "ds"
Set display scale, can be linear: \f(CW\*(C`lin\*(C'\fR or log: \f(CW\*(C`log\*(C'\fR,
default is \f(CW\*(C`lin\*(C'\fR.
