.SS "showwaves"
.IX Subsection "showwaves"
Convert input audio to a video output, representing the samples waves.
.PP
The filter accepts the following options:
.IP "\fBsize, s\fR" 4
.IX Item "size, s"
Specify the video size for the output. For the syntax of this option, check the
\&\fB\*(L"Video size\*(R" section in the ffmpeg-utils manual\fR.
Default value is \f(CW\*(C`600x240\*(C'\fR.
.IP "\fBmode\fR" 4
.IX Item "mode"
Set display mode.
.Sp
Available values are:
.RS 4
.IP "\fBpoint\fR" 4
.IX Item "point"
Draw a point for each sample.
.IP "\fBline\fR" 4
.IX Item "line"
Draw a vertical line for each sample.
.IP "\fBp2p\fR" 4
.IX Item "p2p"
Draw a point for each sample and a line between them.
.IP "\fBcline\fR" 4
.IX Item "cline"
Draw a centered vertical line for each sample.
.RE
.RS 4
.Sp
Default value is \f(CW\*(C`point\*(C'\fR.
.RE
.IP "\fBn\fR" 4
.IX Item "n"
Set the number of samples which are printed on the same column. A
larger value will decrease the frame rate. Must be a positive
integer. This option can be set only if the value for \fIrate\fR
is not explicitly specified.
.IP "\fBrate, r\fR" 4
.IX Item "rate, r"
Set the (approximate) output frame rate. This is done by setting the
option \fIn\fR. Default value is \*(L"25\*(R".
.IP "\fBsplit_channels\fR" 4
.IX Item "split_channels"
Set if channels should be drawn separately or overlap. Default value is 0.
.IP "\fBcolors\fR" 4
.IX Item "colors"
Set colors separated by '|' which are going to be used for drawing of each channel.
.IP "\fBscale\fR" 4
.IX Item "scale"
Set amplitude scale.
.Sp
Available values are:
.RS 4
.IP "\fBlin\fR" 4
.IX Item "lin"
Linear.
.IP "\fBlog\fR" 4
.IX Item "log"
Logarithmic.
.IP "\fBsqrt\fR" 4
.IX Item "sqrt"
Square root.
.IP "\fBcbrt\fR" 4
.IX Item "cbrt"
Cubic root.
.RE
.RS 4
.Sp
Default is linear.
.RE
.IP "\fBdraw\fR" 4
.IX Item "draw"
Set the draw mode. This is mostly useful to set for high \fIn\fR.
.Sp
Available values are:
.RS 4
.IP "\fBscale\fR" 4
.IX Item "scale"
Scale pixel values for each drawn sample.
.IP "\fBfull\fR" 4
.IX Item "full"
Draw every sample directly.
.RE
.RS 4
.Sp
Default value is \f(CW\*(C`scale\*(C'\fR.
.RE
.PP
